org.jamsim.ascape.navigator

Class MicroSimScapeNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.tree.DefaultMutableTreeNode
      • org.jamsim.ascape.navigator.MicroSimScapeNode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, MutableTreeNode, TreeNode

    public class MicroSimScapeNode
extends DefaultMutableTreeNode
    Navigator tree node for a MicroSimScape. Same as ScapeNode but in addition:
    • creates a "Datasets" node child with PanelViewNodes for all the data in the scape
    • creates an "Output Tables" node and exposes access to this node so scapes can add tables during or after the simulation run
    Version:
    $Revision$
    Author:
    Oliver Mannion
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • addUserNode

        public void addUserNode(OutputDatasetProvider provider,
               String path)
        Add a dataset node under "User Tables". The node is automatically opened after it is added. Takes a provider instead of a dataset directly, so the provider can serve up whatever it wants each time the node is opened. Takes a OutputDatasetNodeProvider instead of a PanelViewProvider because a dataset is the most likely type of node to be produced and we can do the wrapping in a PanelView for the caller.
        Parameters:
        provider - provider
        path - a path to a sub folder node, eg: "Base/Means" which represents the folder Means under the folder Base, or just "Base" which will add to the folder Base, or null to add directly under "User Tables".
